      "description": "Presenting a concours-level 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S. This 996.2 variant features the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six with VarioCam Plus, delivering 320hp through a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The Viscous Multi-Plate AWD system ensures optimal torque distribution across the wide-body chassis. Mechanically flawless, the IMS bearing has been proactively retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the Rear Main Seal is bone dry. The suspension remains taut with factory-spec Bilstein dampers, while the braking system features red four-piston monobloc calipers clamping ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. Finished in Arctic Silver over Graphite Grey leather, the paint depth is consistent with zero oxidation or road rash. A true turn-key investment for the discerning purist seeking peak analog performance.",
